cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.MM

This paper proposes a hierarchical deep generative model for piecewise smooth signals, which is closely related to multilayer-convolutional sparse coding (ML-CSC) generative model for deep networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of filters and sparse coding, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper uses MNIST for classification, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
